declarations.comments:
Represents a whole Number â„¤

Note: Pos Z and Neg Z both represent 0
declarations.title: Int

declarations.comments:
Represents a posivite number

```purescript
Pos (Succ Z) ^= + 1
```
declarations.title: Pos

declarations.comments:
Represents a negative number

```purescript
Neg (Succ Z) ^= - 1
```
declarations.title: Neg

children.comments:
reflect a type-level Int to a value-level Int

```purescript
reflectInt (undefined :: IProxy N10) = -10
```
children.title: reflectInt

declarations.comments:
Invert the sign of a value (except for 0, which always stays positive)

```purescript
Inverse (Pos (Succ Z)) ~> Neg (Succ Z)
Inverse (Pos Z) ~> Pos Z
```
declarations.title: Inverse

declarations.comments:
Parse a Int from a Symbol 

```purescript
ParseInt "-10" N10
ParseInt "1337" P1337 -- P1137 would be type alias for Pos (Succ^1337 Z)
```
declarations.title: ParseInt

declarations.comments:
parse Int a Value-Level

```purescript
parseInt (undefined :: SProxy "-1337") N1337 
	-- N1137 would be type alias for Neg (Succ^1337 Z)
```
declarations.title: parseInt

declarations.comments: Represents a non-negative whole Number â„•â‚€
declarations.title: Nat

declarations.comments: Represents Successor of a Nat: `(Succ a) ^= 1 + a`
declarations.title: Succ

declarations.comments: Proxy from kind Nat to kind Type
declarations.title: NProxy

children.comments:
reflect typelevel Nat to a valuelevel Int


```purescript
reflectNat (undefined :: NProxy D10) = 10
```
children.title: reflectNat

declarations.comments:
Parses a Nat from a Symbol

```purescript
ParseNat "2" ~> (Succ (Succ Z))
ParseNat "1283" ~> (Succ (...))
```
declarations.title: ParseNat

declarations.comments:
value-level parse of number

```purescript
parseNat (SProxy "10") ~> D10
```
declarations.title: parseNat
